   Here is the 57-37 roll call by which the Senate
failed to end a filibuster on a wide-ranging crime bill which
included proposed bans on nine categories of semiautomatic weapons.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to curtail debate and a
``no'' vote was a vote to continue the filibuster.
   Voting ``yes'' were 46 Democrats and 11 Republicans.
   Voting ``no'' were 7 Democrats and 30 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
